WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.440
Kingdom of Science Drama Club First Performance
"The Mysterious Light"

00:00:08.100 --> 00:00:11.530
Why did he want us all here?

00:00:11.940 --> 00:00:13.150
Performance?

00:00:13.480 --> 00:00:14.860
"Mysterious Light"?

00:00:14.860 --> 00:00:17.020
One day, thousands of years ago...

00:00:21.700 --> 00:00:25.820
The planet was engulfed 
in a mysterious light.

00:00:35.330 --> 00:00:36.260
Oh, shit!

00:00:36.260 --> 00:00:38.460
This is really bad!

00:00:40.220 --> 00:00:45.100
And so all of humanity was turned to stone.

00:00:49.330 --> 00:00:54.100
Every last piece of civilization that 
had been built up until then collapsed.

00:00:56.690 --> 00:01:00.160
But there was one man who refused to give up,

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:03.530
and prepared himself for his own reawakening.

00:01:04.670 --> 00:01:05.620
That man was...

00:01:11.810 --> 00:01:14.820
A boy of science, Ishigami Senku.

00:01:14.820 --> 00:01:18.780
One, two, three,

00:01:18.780 --> 00:01:25.270
four, five, six, seven, eight...

00:01:19.230 --> 00:01:25.270
Senku held on to his consciousness, 
continuing to count for thousands of years.

00:01:25.490 --> 00:01:28.230
Crackle, crackle, crackle!

00:01:28.630 --> 00:01:29.440
Hm?

00:01:29.440 --> 00:01:30.940
What's this?

00:01:30.940 --> 00:01:34.070
The whole world's stone, damn it!

00:01:38.180 --> 00:01:41.420
All right, I'm going to climb right back

00:01:41.420 --> 00:01:44.330
to the top of humanity's 
two-million-year tech tree!

00:01:44.510 --> 00:01:48.540
And we're going to use science to figure 
out how to undo the petrification.

00:01:48.540 --> 00:01:51.480
Time to build civilization up from scratch!

00:01:56.830 --> 00:01:59.760
Senku and Taiju continue their research.

00:02:03.150 --> 00:02:06.140
The revival fluid works! 
We can un-petrify people!

00:02:07.970 --> 00:02:11.100
And after a fierce battle 
with the Tsukasa Empire,

00:02:11.100 --> 00:02:13.900
the time has finally come 
to tackle <i>the</i> mystery.

00:02:15.160 --> 00:02:15.970
Yeah.

00:02:15.970 --> 00:02:19.060
To solve the mystery, we're headed 
to the other side of the planet,

00:02:19.060 --> 00:02:22.040
where the petrification beam came from!

00:02:22.040 --> 00:02:23.030
What?!

00:02:23.030 --> 00:02:25.640
Th-The other side of the planet, you say?!

00:02:25.640 --> 00:02:28.160
But h-how do we do that?

00:02:31.030 --> 00:02:34.510
We're all going to build a ship together!

00:02:35.700 --> 00:02:39.090
This is exhilarating!

00:02:43.110 --> 00:02:44.090
Senku...

00:02:44.090 --> 00:02:46.230
He might be able to do it.

00:02:46.230 --> 00:02:48.590
He might even solve the 
mystery behind the light.

00:02:48.590 --> 00:02:50.020
Heya!

00:02:50.850 --> 00:02:57.740
If you've been totally confused this 
whole time, you're one of us now.

00:02:57.960 --> 00:03:02.320
So can we count on you to help out?

00:03:02.320 --> 00:03:03.030
Yeah!

00:03:03.030 --> 00:03:05.200
Time to take back civilization!

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:06.290
We got this!

00:03:08.230 --> 00:03:11.170
He's raising morale by sharing information.

00:03:11.170 --> 00:03:12.980
That's our Gen.

00:03:12.980 --> 00:03:14.640
Stage plays!

00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:15.930
I love it.

00:03:15.930 --> 00:03:17.500
That was powerful.

00:03:17.500 --> 00:03:21.110
Well then, everyone, since we're 
all building our ship together,

00:03:21.110 --> 00:03:24.010
it's time to start pitting our 
ideas against each other's!

00:03:28.580 --> 00:03:30.650
Damn it, Gen...

00:03:30.650 --> 00:03:34.120
This confetti is ten billion 
percent way too extra.

00:03:35.510 --> 00:03:37.350
Don't say that, Senku-chan.

00:03:37.350 --> 00:03:39.740
We're trying to set a mood here.

00:03:42.580 --> 00:03:43.950
Magma and Yo?

00:03:43.950 --> 00:03:46.040
I wasn't expecting those two, either.

00:03:46.040 --> 00:03:51.080
They always look like slobs, 
but they look really smart today!

00:03:51.080 --> 00:03:54.190
The people of Ishigami Village 
are people of the sea.

00:03:54.190 --> 00:03:56.350
Ships are right in our wheelhouse.

00:03:56.350 --> 00:03:59.100
The throne is mine now!

00:04:01.940 --> 00:04:04.780
This is finally my chance!

00:04:04.780 --> 00:04:08.060
Once I win here, I'll be right at the top.

00:04:08.060 --> 00:04:14.230
All right, let's have the three 
of you present your ideas!

00:04:17.060 --> 00:04:21.030
Why do we even need a competition, anyway?

00:04:21.030 --> 00:04:23.660
Senku's obviously going to win.

00:04:23.660 --> 00:04:25.590
Yeah, it's strange.

00:04:26.050 --> 00:04:28.700
Especially since he must want 
to leave as soon as we can.

00:04:29.700 --> 00:04:31.370
Huh? Yo-chan?

00:04:32.620 --> 00:04:35.210
You'll want to see my presentation last.

00:04:35.880 --> 00:04:40.250
My ship's already finished, after all.

00:04:40.250 --> 00:04:42.950
Seeing is believing, right?

00:04:43.310 --> 00:04:46.790
Whoever can build the thing and 
show it off first is going to win.

00:04:50.210 --> 00:04:52.840
You primitives aren't going to have much...

00:04:54.420 --> 00:04:58.080
Nah. I shouldn't be laughing 
at the underdeveloped.

00:05:03.330 --> 00:05:04.700
Awesome!

00:05:06.500 --> 00:05:08.480
The village is full of boats.

00:05:08.480 --> 00:05:11.240
I've seen way too many of them.

00:05:14.490 --> 00:05:17.870
This gets me pumped to see Yo's ship, too!

00:05:17.870 --> 00:05:20.740
You did say "seeing is believing," didn't you?

00:05:20.740 --> 00:05:22.530
With that smug look on your face.

00:05:22.530 --> 00:05:23.850
You sure did.

00:05:23.850 --> 00:05:25.390
Hurry up and show us!

00:05:26.540 --> 00:05:28.670
I never said such a thing.

00:05:28.670 --> 00:05:30.500
Wait, did I?

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:31.530
Oh, crap!

00:05:31.530 --> 00:05:33.520
I left it at home!

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:38.680
Hey, it's like a tiny raft thing.

00:05:44.200 --> 00:05:46.330
Senku-chan, what's up?

00:05:46.330 --> 00:05:49.070
Are the sails made of straw?

00:05:50.010 --> 00:05:51.260
Made of what, now?

00:05:51.950 --> 00:05:53.790
Is it sewn from straw?

00:05:53.790 --> 00:05:56.290
Yeah, something like that, I guess.

00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:00.980
This is insanely useful, Magma.

00:06:00.980 --> 00:06:02.460
You're right.

00:06:02.460 --> 00:06:04.670
You really are people of the sea.

00:06:04.670 --> 00:06:07.460
Experience is worth its weight in gold.

00:06:07.460 --> 00:06:11.430
If we know that straw 
sails are good enough...

00:06:13.550 --> 00:06:16.300
We can definitely start building this ship.

00:06:16.930 --> 00:06:18.440
That's it!

00:06:19.190 --> 00:06:20.630
Damn it!

00:06:20.630 --> 00:06:22.320
He went all-out!

00:06:22.320 --> 00:06:25.480
That's obviously what we want, 
if we can build it!

00:06:26.850 --> 00:06:28.740
It's a proper sailboat.

00:06:29.160 --> 00:06:34.250
It looks cool as hell, but how many hundreds 
of years are we going to spend on it?

00:06:34.250 --> 00:06:37.320
I'll die of old age before it's done!

00:06:37.320 --> 00:06:38.750
Don't do this to me!

00:06:38.750 --> 00:06:41.750
Unless we had, like, a hundred 
people to help build it...

00:06:43.390 --> 00:06:45.610
Wake up, all of you.

00:06:46.770 --> 00:06:50.570
What do you think that 
stupid stage play was for?

00:06:55.220 --> 00:07:02.010
We've got all those strapping men on our 
side that Tsukasa-sensei woke up for us.

00:07:03.140 --> 00:07:06.190
We have a hybrid of science 
and strength in our manpower.

00:07:06.360 --> 00:07:08.300
This is going to be exhilarating!

00:07:25.350 --> 00:07:27.810
Getting to the other side of the planet

00:07:27.810 --> 00:07:30.220
should be easy on a ship like this one, right?

00:07:30.410 --> 00:07:32.580
Yeah, as long as we can get access

00:07:32.580 --> 00:07:37.100
to one more special talent. 
We're ten billion percent going to need it.

00:07:43.870 --> 00:07:46.880
Tsuka-san...

00:07:46.880 --> 00:07:49.240
Buck up already.

00:07:50.360 --> 00:07:50.690
Huh?

00:07:51.050 --> 00:07:52.870
Tsukasa told me about you.

00:07:52.870 --> 00:07:55.950
You're the information broker 
who knew who to revive?

00:07:57.000 --> 00:07:59.790
I have a job for you, journalist.

00:08:00.900 --> 00:08:02.050
Journalist...

00:08:04.460 --> 00:08:06.310
Human contact...

00:08:06.870 --> 00:08:08.410
Information about people...

00:08:08.910 --> 00:08:11.530
Those were my weapons as a journalist.

00:08:12.780 --> 00:08:14.570
Who do you want?

00:08:15.180 --> 00:08:17.550
I'll find whoever it is you're after.

00:08:19.740 --> 00:08:21.730
I want a captain.

00:08:23.110 --> 00:08:26.060
This'll be a make-or-break Age of Discovery 
voyage across the planet.

00:08:26.060 --> 00:08:29.400
We need a captain with 
ten billion skill points in sailing.

00:08:29.750 --> 00:08:34.700
They'll be the key to reviving all of humanity.

00:08:34.700 --> 00:08:37.420
That's who we need on our team.

00:08:43.820 --> 00:08:45.070
I see it.

00:08:45.070 --> 00:08:46.250
That's the island.

00:08:47.630 --> 00:08:49.500
Wait for us, Captain!

00:08:49.890 --> 00:08:50.920
Although...

00:08:50.920 --> 00:08:54.020
We're making a sailboat.

00:08:52.050 --> 00:08:58.010
Modern Ships

00:08:52.050 --> 00:08:58.010
Sailboats

00:08:52.050 --> 00:08:58.010
Wind-powered

00:08:54.020 --> 00:08:56.780
Are we sure we can find someone 
who has that kind of experience?

00:08:56.780 --> 00:08:58.010
A modern person, I mean.

00:08:58.420 --> 00:09:01.170
Probably only for training purposes.

00:09:01.170 --> 00:09:06.190
I don't think we'd find anyone anywhere in 
the world who's been sailing all the time.

00:09:09.790 --> 00:09:11.280
Ryusu—

00:09:12.460 --> 00:09:13.320
Ryusu?

00:09:13.500 --> 00:09:15.110
No, never mind!

00:09:15.110 --> 00:09:17.180
Let's go! Hurry!

00:09:21.410 --> 00:09:22.740
Nanami Academy.

00:09:22.910 --> 00:09:28.030
Nautical schools like this 
one usually teach sailing.

00:09:28.030 --> 00:09:32.120
One of the teachers would probably 
know how to steer one, at least.

00:09:37.150 --> 00:09:39.240
All right, time to mine stone statues.

00:09:39.240 --> 00:09:42.130
Dig, dig, and dig some more, Team Gorillas!

00:09:42.130 --> 00:09:44.190
We'll take care of it!

00:09:44.190 --> 00:09:46.180
I'm not a gorilla, m'kay?

00:09:57.460 --> 00:09:59.230
Are we waking up all of them?

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:02.320
No. We're running out of revival fluid,

00:10:02.320 --> 00:10:05.720
thanks to Homura wrecking the miracle cave.

00:10:06.290 --> 00:10:10.700
Guess we'll have to choose a good 
middle-ground with plenty of experience, then.

00:10:10.700 --> 00:10:14.630
I know a few of the instructors 
from when I came to do a report.

00:10:19.260 --> 00:10:20.520
There he is.

00:10:20.520 --> 00:10:21.510
Ryusui...

00:10:22.590 --> 00:10:24.010
You said that name before, too.

00:10:24.190 --> 00:10:25.250
No, no!

00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:26.680
You really don't want him!

00:10:26.680 --> 00:10:30.190
Quit mumbling and just speak.

00:10:31.030 --> 00:10:33.390
He's got talent, right?

00:10:33.390 --> 00:10:35.690
That must be why you blurted out his name.

00:10:39.400 --> 00:10:44.910
Nanami Academy was owned by the king of 
maritime trade, the Nanami Conglomerate.

00:10:44.910 --> 00:10:47.550
They had 200 trillion yen in assets.

00:10:47.550 --> 00:10:51.460
And he's the hopelessly self-indulgent 
son of the Nanami family.

00:10:51.460 --> 00:10:52.860
Nanami Ryusui.

00:10:53.350 --> 00:10:56.740
He'd apparently been spending his 
hundreds of millions of yen in allowance

00:10:56.740 --> 00:11:00.120
to collect model ships and bottle 
ships since he was a kid.

00:11:00.120 --> 00:11:02.340
H-Hundreds of millions in <i>allowance</i>?!

00:11:02.550 --> 00:11:06.810
He could never get enough, so eventually, 
he had a real sailboat built for him.

00:11:06.810 --> 00:11:09.530
Ever since he was in middle school,

00:11:09.530 --> 00:11:13.650
he'd been sailing around the world 
seeking pleasure, without any help.

00:11:13.650 --> 00:11:15.530
A captain since middle school?!

00:11:15.530 --> 00:11:17.060
He's the real deal!

00:11:17.060 --> 00:11:19.610
Nothing's more valuable than experience.

00:11:19.610 --> 00:11:23.060
Didn't I tell you he's 
hopelessly self-indulgent?

00:11:23.060 --> 00:11:25.560
Tsukasa hated him for being 
an established power, too.

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:27.990
I would choose someone else.

00:11:27.990 --> 00:11:31.100
We won't find anyone who's a more 
skilled sailor than Ryusui-kun,

00:11:31.100 --> 00:11:34.250
but we won't find anyone who's got a 
personality worse than his, either.

00:11:34.250 --> 00:11:36.860
The ultimate dilemma...

00:11:36.860 --> 00:11:39.090
Do we take a proper, 
reasonably talented person,

00:11:39.090 --> 00:11:42.010
or do we take the risky one 
with top-of-the-line skill?

00:11:43.430 --> 00:11:45.350
He's already using the revival fluid on him!

00:11:46.940 --> 00:11:50.310
Talent comes first, obviously.

00:12:15.130 --> 00:12:17.250
I'm back at last!

00:12:18.460 --> 00:12:21.400
